## Revolutionary Sprint Backlog

### Epic: ComponentForge Visual Builder
**Story Points: 10**

#### GUI-REV-001: Component Canvas System
**Points: 6 | Priority: Critical**

**Description:** Build the revolutionary component canvas where users compose experiments visually by dragging and connecting components.

**Revolutionary Features:**
- GPU-accelerated component rendering with WebGL2
- Real-time component connections and data flow visualization
- Physics-based component interaction (snap, magnetism, collision)
- Multi-touch gesture support for component manipulation
- Infinite canvas with smooth zoom/pan (0.1x to 10x)
- Component hierarchy visualization with tree/graph views

**Technical Requirements:**
```typescript
// Revolutionary Component Canvas
interface ComponentCanvas {
  // GPU-accelerated rendering
  renderer: WebGL2Renderer;

  // Physics-based interactions
  physics: ComponentPhysicsEngine;

  // Real-time component system
  componentSystem: ComponentSystem;

  // Gesture recognition
  gestureHandler: GestureRecognitionSystem;

  // Performance monitoring
  performanceMonitor: CanvasPerformanceMonitor;
}

// Component manipulation with μs-precision
class ComponentManipulator {
  dragComponent(component: BaseComponent, startPos: Vector2, endPos: Vector2): void;
  connectComponents(source: BaseComponent, target: BaseComponent): void;
  animateTransition(component: BaseComponent, animation: ComponentAnimation): void;
}
```

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Component canvas renders at 144fps on target hardware
- [ ] Drag-and-drop operations complete within 2ms
- [ ] Component connections visualized with animated data flows
- [ ] Gesture recognition supports multi-touch manipulation
- [ ] Canvas scales smoothly from 0.1x to 10x zoom
- [ ] Component physics feel natural and responsive
- [ ] WebGL2 fallback to WebGL1/Canvas2D gracefully

**Revolutionary Canvas Architecture:**
```svelte
<!-- ComponentCanvas.svelte -->
<script lang="ts">
  import { onMount } from 'svelte';
  import { ComponentCanvas, WebGL2Renderer } from '$lib/canvas';
  import type { ComponentForge } from '@psyforge/forgescript';

  export let forge: ComponentForge;

  let canvasElement: HTMLCanvasElement;
  let canvas: ComponentCanvas;

  onMount(async () => {
    canvas = new ComponentCanvas(canvasElement, {
      enableGPUAcceleration: true,
      enablePhysics: true,
      targetFPS: 144,
      maxFrameTime: 2,
    });

    await canvas.initialize(forge);
  });

  function handleComponentDrop(event: ComponentDropEvent) {
    canvas.addComponent(event.component, event.position);
  }

  function handleComponentConnect(event: ComponentConnectEvent) {
    canvas.connectComponents(event.source, event.target);
  }
</script>

<canvas
  bind:this={canvasElement}
  class="component-canvas w-full h-full"
  on:componentdrop={handleComponentDrop}
  on:componentconnect={handleComponentConnect}
/>
```

